Oluwatosin Omojuyigbe A member of the Lagos State House of Assembly representing the Kosofe Constituency 2, Tunde Buraimoh, has urged Nigerians to demonstrate genuine love and concern towards one another for the country to experience a great turnaround. Buraimoh stated this at the 43rd Annual Lewu Day Thanksgiving Celebrations of the Odolewu community in Ogun State. Buraimoh, who represented the senator representing the Lagos-East at the Senate, Adebayo Osinowo, at the event, urged Nigerians to reflect on their past relationship with God and genuinely reconcile with Him to enable the country to attain its economic growth among other nations globally. He said, “I want to plead with us to fervently continue in our prayers for God’s divine intervention and our unflinching support to the country’s leaders. It is with the upliftment of our nation’s economy through such genuine love and transparency,that we will always appreciate God’s glory and grace in us.” In his welcome address at the event, a community leader, Anthony Adefuye, urged members of the community at home and in the Diaspora, to encourage their children to regularly identify with the community. Copyright PUNCH.
